EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to posting information regarding preventing the spread of communicable diseases at schools and day care centers.
EventItemMatterName: Posting information regarding preventing the spread of communicable diseases at schools and day care centers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting smoking on and around hospital grounds.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting smoking on and around hospital grounds.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the City Administrative Procedure Act of the New York City Charter, to require that all agencies electronically transmit copies of proposed rules in a timely manner.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the City Administrative Procedure Act of the NYC Charter, to require that all agencies electronically transmit copies of proposed rules in a timely manner.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Senate to pass S.2811, which would create a rehabilitation program of civic service, education, and job training to assist non-violent felony offenders reintegrate successfully into society.
EventItemMatterName: Create a rehabilitation program of civic service, education, and job training to assist non-violent felony offenders reintegrate successfully into society. (S.2811)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the establishment of a voluntary emergency medical service patient registry.
EventItemMatterName: Establishment of a voluntary emergency medical service patient registry.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to emergency evacuation and community notification plans for certain buildings that have received a variance to store diesel fuel or store more than a threshold amount of diesel fuel.
EventItemMatterName: Emergency evacuation and community notification plans for certain buildings that have received a variance to store diesel fuel or store more than a threshold amount of diesel fuel.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Congress to pass and President George W. Bush to approve legislation extending the right of first refusal to federally funded Project-based Section 8 developments.
EventItemMatterName: Approve legislation extending the right of first refusal to federally funded Project-based Section 8 developments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for changes in the New York City Family Court system to better protect battered women and parents who reasonably believe that their child is threatened by child abuse or domestic violence that is perpetrated or permitted by the child’s other parent.
EventItemMatterName: Changes in the New York City Family Court system to better protect battered women and parents who reasonably believe that their child is threatened by child abuse or domestic violence.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to make nurses available to public and private high schools.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to make nurses available to public and private high schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the installation of nitrous oxide tanks in automobiles.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the installation of nitrous oxide tanks in automobiles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing legal counsel for certain tenants subject to eviction, ejectment or foreclosure proceedings.
EventItemMatterName: Providing legal counsel for certain tenants subject to eviction, ejectment or foreclosure proceedings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass S.1113/H.R.2048, also known as the “Traumatic Brain Injury Access to Options Act.”
EventItemMatterName: Traumatic Brain Injury Access to Options Act.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing information to schools regarding communicable diseases.
EventItemMatterName: Providing information to schools regarding communicable diseases.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution endorsing the Speaker’s decision to file, on behalf of the Council, an amicus brief in support of the Plaintiffs in the litigation between several states and the federal government captioned New York v. U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, for the purpose of supporting the wide latitude granted to states by the State Children’s Health Insurance Program (“SCHIP”) to set their own income rules for SCHIP eligibility.
EventItemMatterName: Speaker’s decision to file, on behalf of the Council, an amicus brief in support of the Plaintiffs in the litigation between several states and the federal government captioned New York v. U.S. Department of Health and Human Services.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign into law the Paycheck Fairness Act.
EventItemMatterName: Paycheck Fairness Act

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to biological, chemical and radiological detectors.
EventItemMatterName: Permits for atmospheric biological, chemical and radiological detectors.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass the “Thomas J. Manton Prostate Cancer Early Detection and Treatment Act of 2007” (S. 1275 and H.R. 2131), which would amend the Public Health Service Act and Title XIX of the Social Security Act to provide for a screening and treatment program for prostate cancer in the same manner as is provided for breast and cervical cancer.
EventItemMatterName: Thomas J. Manton Prostate Cancer Early Detection and Treatment Act of 2007. (S.1275/H.R.2131)
